Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 31, 11, 116, 6 or 201, 49. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0392.36.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0398)
